ETYMOLOGY: From Late Latin incompletu (not complete), from Latin in- (not) + completus (complete), past participle of complere (to fill up, complete).

MEANINGS.POS_TIP: An adjective describes or modifies a noun or pronoun.
MEANINGS.DEF_EN: Not finished; not having all its parts; lacking something.
MEANINGS.DEF_ZH: 未完成的；不完整的；缺乏某些部分的。
MEANINGS.SENT_EN: The project remains incomplete due to insufficient funding.
MEANINGS.SENT_ZH: 由于资金不足，该项目仍未完成。
